<TITLE> Businessman killed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbaria, May 15 (bdnews24.com)An organised gang of criminals killed a businessman in Brahmanbaria on Friday night. Kajal Das, 45, of Fandauk village of Nasirnagar Upazila, got on a microbus for home from Narsingdi, Golam Faruk, a Union Parishad chairman, said. But the criminals, pretending to be co-passengers, drugged him and took his cash, mobile-phone set and gold bracelet before dumping him on the highway near Brahmanbaria. An ill Kajal was pronounced dead on arrival at Brahmanbaria Sadar Hospital, Faruk added. bdnews24
